@startuml
' @id(USE-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE)
' @id(USE-DEPLOY-INSPECT)
'
' Objective-side use cases for the new /mdd-deploy utility skill. This is
' a STANDALONE skill, a sibling of /mdd-render: it is NOT wired into
' /mdd-cycle, /mdd-map, /mdd-validate, or /mdd-review and never touches
' the current<->objective parity gate. It guides an Azure Container Apps
' deployment of a target repo; it never executes a deploy command.
'
' @desc(USE-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE, "Operator runs /mdd-deploy with a one-line deployment description; the skill produces a UML deployment diagram, generated Bicep IaC, and an explicit copy-pasteable command runbook that preserves the target's security invariants. The skill executes nothing — the human runs the commands.")
' @desc(USE-DEPLOY-INSPECT, "Operator inspects the generated deployment diagram visually: /mdd-render is extended to also rasterize .mdd/deploy/**/*.puml to .mdd/rendered/deploy/**/*.svg. Additive and non-gating.")
title /mdd-deploy deployment guidance — use cases (objective)

left to right direction

actor "Operator" as Op

rectangle "mdd toolchain (utility, outside the parity gate)" {
  usecase "Guide an Azure Container Apps\ndeployment via a diagram,\nrunbook, and generated IaC" as Guide
  usecase "Inspect the generated\ndeployment diagram as SVG" as Inspect
}

Op --> Guide
Op --> Inspect

Guide ..> Inspect : <<extend>>

note bottom of Guide
  v1 supports exactly one target:
  azure-container-apps (../atlas-ate-server).
  Any other target -> "not yet supported", stop.
  Reads .mdd/models components+use-cases and the
  target repo (README, Dockerfile, compose,
  .env.example, src) READ-ONLY for topology and
  security invariants. PAUSES and asks the user
  whenever a topology or security choice is
  genuinely ambiguous (same discipline as
  /mdd-cycle). Writes the deployment diagram +
  runbook + generated infra; then reports and
  STOPS. It NEVER runs az / docker / brew.
  The diagram's <<Encrypt>>/<<ByPassing>>/...
  stereotypes are DOCUMENTATION ONLY — they are
  NOT the gated security-marker parity mechanism.
  Realized by SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE.
end note

note bottom of Inspect
  Not a gate. /mdd-validate, /mdd-review and the
  /mdd-cycle parity loop never read .mdd/deploy/.
  Realized by SEQ-DEPLOY-INSPECT.
end note
@enduml
